---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Free Online PDF Compressor - Zcompressor | Compress PDF Free"
  description="Use Zcompressor, the best free online PDF compressor, to reduce PDF file size online for free. Compress PDF files securely client-side with no server uploads. Fast, private, and unlimited."
  keywords="pdf compressor, pdf compressor free, free pdf compressor, online pdf compressor, pdf compressor online free, free online pdf compressor"
  ogUrl="https://Zcompressor.com"
  ogType="website"
>

  <!-- JSON-LD FAQ Schema for SEO -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best free pdf compressor?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Zcompressor is widely considered the best free PDF compressor available. It operates entirely client-side inside your web browser, ensuring that your documents are processed with 100% privacy and never uploaded to any remote servers. It is completely free, has no file size limits, requires no email registration, and leaves no watermarks.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best pdf compressor for large files?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The best PDF compressor for large files is Zcompressor. Because it performs compression locally in your browser's memory (RAM), it avoids slow internet upload speeds and remote server timeouts. This makes it exceptionally fast and reliable for large scanned documents, portfolios, and presentations under 100MB.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what does a pdf compressor do?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A PDF compressor reduces the total file size of PDF documents. It does this by compressing embedded images, downsampling visual content (reducing resolution or DPI), removing duplicate fonts, and cleaning up unused objects or metadata from the internal PDF structure.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is a pdf compressor",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A PDF compressor is a software application or online utility designed to shrink the file size of PDF (Portable Document Format) files, making them easier to email, store, or upload to web portals.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best pdf compressor available?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The best PDF compressor available is one that guarantees privacy and security, such as Zcompressor. It offers unlimited local processing in browser memory without sending your sensitive information to external servers.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best free pdf compressor",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Zcompressor is the ultimate free PDF compressor, offering high-performance compression entirely client-side without registration, subscriptions, or watermarks.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is pdf compressor",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A PDF compressor is a program or web tool that optimizes the code and downsamples images inside a PDF file to reduce its overall storage size.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "pdf compressor how to compress pdf",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To compress a PDF with Zcompressor: drag and drop your files into the compressor, choose a target file size preset, click \"Compress All Files\", and download the optimized PDF individually or as a combined ZIP archive.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "pdf how to compressor",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Compressing a PDF is done by uploading it to a compression tool like Zcompressor, which will automatically reduce the size of visual assets and clean up structural metadata to produce a smaller file.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best pdf compressor?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Zcompressor is the best PDF compressor for users seeking security, speed, and privacy. Because it processes documents locally, your files never touch a remote server.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "which is the best pdf compressor?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Zcompressor is widely recognized as the best PDF compressor because of its absolute client-side privacy, ease of use, fast batch processing, and high quality presets.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "which is the best pdf compressor",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The best PDF compressor is Zcompressor, which offers zero server uploads, no page limits, and custom target size controls for free.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "how does a pdf compressor work",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A PDF compressor works by optimizing the internal elements of a PDF document: it downsamples and re-compresses embedded images to match your target file size, and cleans up redundant structural data such as metadata and duplicate fonts.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "how to use pdf compressor",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Using Zcompressor is simple: drop your PDF files into the tool, select a preset (High, Recommended, or Low), click \"Compress All Files\", and download the resulting smaller files.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "how to compressor pdf",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To compress a PDF, simply drag and drop the document into the Zcompressor tool, choose your desired compression level, and click compress to execute the local conversion.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "what is the best pdf compressor",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Zcompressor is considered the best PDF compressor because it is free, unlimited, secure, and processes files completely locally inside your browser.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

  <Header />

  <!-- Hero Section with Mesh Gradient -->
  <section
    class="relative bg-mesh-gradient overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24 px-4 md:px-6 border-b border-hairline"
  >
    <!-- Background grid overlay -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-grid-pattern opacity-[0.35] dark:opacity-[0.25] pointer-events-none z-0"></div>
    <!-- Spotlight gradient overlay -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-radial-spotlight pointer-events-none z-0"></div>

    <!-- Decorative glowing background orbs -->
    <div class="absolute top-1/4 left-1/4 w-[320px] h-[320px] rounded-full bg-cyan/10 dark:bg-cyan/5 blur-[100px] pointer-events-none z-0 animate-pulse hidden md:block" style="animation-duration: 8s;"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-1/4 right-1/4 w-[360px] h-[360px] rounded-full bg-highlight-pink/8 dark:bg-highlight-pink/4 blur-[120px] pointer-events-none z-0 animate-pulse hidden md:block" style="animation-duration: 12s;"></div>

    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto text-center relative z-10">
      <!-- Eyebrow Badge -->
      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3.5 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-canvas/60 dark:bg-canvas-soft-2/40 backdrop-blur-md border border-hairline text-ink mb-6 shadow-level-2 animate-fade-in"
      >
        <span class="relative flex h-2 w-2">
          <span class="animate-ping absolute inline-flex h-full w-full rounded-full bg-cyan-deep opacity-75"></span>
          <span class="relative inline-flex rounded-full h-2 w-2 bg-cyan-deep"></span>
        </span>
        <span class="text-caption font-mono font-medium tracking-wider uppercase text-body"
          >Zero Server Uploads</span
        >
      </div>

      <!-- Headline -->
      <h1
        class="text-display-xl text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-1.5px] md:tracking-[-2.4px] mb-6 leading-tight text-balance"
      >
        Compress PDFs with absolute privacy.
      </h1>

      <!-- Description -->
      <p class="text-body-lg text-body mb-8 max-w-[600px] mx-auto text-balance">
        Run state-of-the-art compression entirely inside your browser. Your
        files never touch any servers. Fast, secure, and completely free.
      </p>

      <!-- Action Button -->
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a
          href="#compressor"
          class="w-full sm:w-auto px-6 h-[48px] bg-primary text-on-primary text-button-lg rounded-pill hover:bg-black transition-all flex items-center justify-center select-none shadow-level-3 hover:scale-[1.02] duration-200 focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
        >
          Open Compressor
        </a>
        <a
          href="#features"
          class="w-full sm:w-auto px-6 h-[48px] bg-canvas text-ink border border-hairline text-button-lg rounded-pill hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-all flex items-center justify-center select-none shadow-level-2 hover:scale-[1.02] duration-200 focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
        >
          Learn How It Works
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Compressor Tool Dashboard -->
  <section
    id="compressor"
    class="py-16 px-6 max-w-[1200px] mx-auto scroll-mt-[64px]"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <!-- Main Compressor Card -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-6">
        <!-- Drag & Drop Zone -->
        <div
          id="dropzone"
          class="relative group border-2 border-dashed border-hairline-strong/60 rounded-lg bg-canvas p-8 sm:p-12 text-center hover:border-primary/50 hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-all duration-300 shadow-level-3 focus-within:border-primary focus-within:ring-2 focus-within:ring-primary/20"
        >
          <input
            type="file"
            id="file-input"
            multiple
            accept=".pdf"
            class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full opacity-0 cursor-pointer z-10 focus:outline-none"
            aria-label="Select PDF files to compress"
          />

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div
              class="w-16 h-16 mx-auto rounded-full bg-canvas-soft border border-hairline flex items-center justify-center group-hover:scale-110 group-hover:border-primary/30 transition-all duration-300 shadow-level-2"
            >
              <i
                class="fa-regular fa-file-pdf text-3xl text-body group-hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="text-body-md-strong text-ink mb-1">
                Drag and drop your PDF files here
              </p>
              <p class="text-body-sm text-body">
                or click to browse from your computer
              </p>
            </div>
            <div
              class="pt-2 flex justify-center gap-3 text-caption text-mute font-mono"
            >
              <span
                ><i
                  class="fa-solid fa-lock text-cyan-deep mr-1"
                  aria-hidden="true"></i> End-to-end Local</span
              >
              <span>•</span>
              <span
                ><i
                  class="fa-solid fa-bolt text-warning-deep mr-1"
                  aria-hidden="true"></i> Multi-file Batch</span
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- File List / Queue -->
        <div
          id="queue-container"
          class="hidden rounded-lg bg-canvas border border-hairline p-4 sm:p-6 shadow-level-3 space-y-4"
        >
          <div
            class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-hairline pb-4"
          >
            <h3
              class="text-display-sm text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.6px] flex items-center gap-2"
            >
              <span>Files Queue</span>
              <span
                id="queue-badge"
                class="px-2 py-0.5 text-caption font-mono border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas-soft"
                >0</span
              >
            </h3>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <button
                id="clear-queue-btn"
                class="px-3 py-1.5 border border-hairline hover:border-error-deep/30 hover:bg-error-soft text-body hover:text-error-deep rounded-sm text-body-sm transition-all flex items-center gap-1.5 focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <i class="fa-regular fa-trash-can text-xs" aria-hidden="true"
                ></i>
                Clear Queue
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Queue List -->
          <div
            id="queue-list"
            class="divide-y divide-hairline max-h-[350px] overflow-y-auto pr-1"
          >
            <!-- Dynamic File Rows -->
          </div>

          <!-- Batch Action Bar -->
          <div
            class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-4 pt-4 border-t border-hairline"
          >
            <div class="text-body-sm text-body w-full sm:w-auto text-left">
              Total input size: <span
                id="total-input-size"
                class="font-mono font-medium text-ink">0 KB</span
              >
              <span id="total-savings-container" class="hidden">
                | New size: <span
                  id="total-output-size"
                  class="font-mono font-medium text-success">0 KB</span
                >
                (<span
                  id="total-savings-pct"
                  class="font-mono font-semibold text-success">-0%</span
                >)
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 w-full sm:w-auto">
              <button
                id="compress-btn"
                class="w-full sm:w-auto px-6 h-[40px] bg-primary text-on-primary text-button-md rounded-pill hover:bg-black transition-all flex items-center justify-center gap-2 shadow-level-3 focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <i class="fa-solid fa-compress" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                Compress All Files
              </button>
              <button
                id="download-zip-btn"
                class="hidden w-full sm:w-auto px-6 h-[40px] bg-canvas text-ink border border-hairline text-button-md rounded-pill hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-all flex items-center justify-center gap-2 shadow-level-2 focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <i class="fa-regular fa-file-archive" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                Download ZIP
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Terminal Output Log Panel -->
        <div
          class="rounded-lg bg-[#121212] text-[#f5f5f5] shadow-level-4 overflow-hidden border border-[#222222]"
        >
          <div
            id="terminal-header"
            class="bg-[#171717] border-b border-[#222222] px-4 py-2.5 flex items-center justify-between select-none cursor-pointer hover:bg-[#1a1a1a] transition-colors"
            role="button"
            aria-expanded="true"
            aria-controls="terminal-logs"
            tabindex="0"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span
                class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-error-deep"
                aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-warning" aria-hidden="true"
              ></span>
              <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-cyan-deep" aria-hidden="true"
              ></span>
              <span class="text-caption-mono text-white/50 ml-2 font-mono"
                >Zcompressor-engine-console</span
              >
              <i
                id="terminal-toggle-icon"
                class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down text-white/40 text-[10px] transition-transform duration-200 ml-1"
                aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </div>
            <button
              id="clear-logs-btn"
              class="text-white/60 hover:text-white transition-colors text-caption-mono font-mono flex items-center gap-1 rounded focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-white focus-visible:outline-none"
              aria-label="Clear Console Logs"
            >
              <i class="fa-solid fa-terminal text-[10px]" aria-hidden="true"
              ></i>
              Clear
            </button>
          </div>
          <div
            id="terminal-logs"
            class="p-4 h-[180px] overflow-y-auto font-mono text-code text-left space-y-1.5 scrollbar-thin scrollbar-thumb-white/10 scrollbar-track-transparent transition-all"
          >
            <div class="text-white/40">
              [SYS] Console ready. Waiting for files to compress…
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Settings & Controls Panel -->
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div
          class="rounded-lg bg-canvas border border-hairline p-4 sm:p-6 shadow-level-3 space-y-6 text-left"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-display-sm text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.6px] flex items-center gap-2 pb-4 border-b border-hairline"
          >
            <i
              class="fa-solid fa-sliders text-body text-base"
              aria-hidden="true"></i>
            Compression Settings
          </h3>

          <!-- Presets -->
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <span class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink block">Target File Size</span>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-1 gap-2">
              <!-- Preset 250 KB -->
              <button
                data-preset="250kb"
                class="preset-btn text-left p-3 rounded border border-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong transition-all flex items-start justify-between group focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <div>
                  <div
                    class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink group-hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                  >
                    250 KB Target
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-caption text-body">
                    Maximum compression. Ideal for strict limits.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas-soft text-body mt-0.5"
                  >250 KB</span
                >
              </button>

              <!-- Preset 500 KB -->
              <button
                data-preset="500kb"
                class="preset-btn text-left p-3 rounded border border-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong transition-all flex items-start justify-between group focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <div>
                  <div
                    class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink group-hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                  >
                    500 KB Target
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-caption text-body">
                    High compression. Great for email attachments.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas-soft text-body mt-0.5"
                  >500 KB</span
                >
              </button>

              <!-- Preset 1 MB -->
              <button
                data-preset="1mb"
                class="preset-btn active text-left p-3 rounded border-2 border-primary bg-canvas-soft transition-all flex items-start justify-between group focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <div>
                  <div
                    class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink flex items-center gap-1.5"
                  >
                    1 MB Target
                    <span
                      class="px-1.5 py-0.2 text-[9px] font-sans font-semibold rounded-full bg-link-bg-soft text-link-deep"
                      >Recommended</span
                    >
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-caption text-body">
                    Balanced visual quality & file size.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas-soft text-body mt-0.5"
                  >1 MB</span
                >
              </button>

              <!-- Preset 2 MB -->
              <button
                data-preset="2mb"
                class="preset-btn text-left p-3 rounded border border-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong transition-all flex items-start justify-between group focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <div>
                  <div
                    class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink group-hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                  >
                    2 MB Target
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-caption text-body">
                    Medium compression. Keeps images sharp.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas-soft text-body mt-0.5"
                  >2 MB</span
                >
              </button>

              <!-- Preset 5 MB -->
              <button
                data-preset="5mb"
                class="preset-btn text-left p-3 rounded border border-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong transition-all flex items-start justify-between group focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <div>
                  <div
                    class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink group-hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                  >
                    5 MB Target
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-caption text-body">
                    Low compression. Best visual quality.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas-soft text-body mt-0.5"
                  >5 MB</span
                >
              </button>

              <!-- Preset Custom -->
              <button
                data-preset="custom"
                class="preset-btn text-left p-3 rounded border border-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong transition-all flex items-start justify-between group focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:outline-none"
              >
                <div>
                  <div
                    class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink group-hover:text-primary transition-colors"
                  >
                    Custom Target Size
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-caption text-body">
                    Specify your own target file size limit.
                  </div>
                </div>
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-mono border border-hairline rounded bg-canvas-soft text-body mt-0.5"
                  >Custom</span
                >
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Custom Settings Controls -->
          <div
            id="custom-sliders"
            class="hidden space-y-4 pt-4 border-t border-hairline animate-fade-in"
          >
            <!-- Target Size Slider -->
            <div class="space-y-2">
              <label
                for="size-slider"
                class="flex justify-between items-center text-body-sm cursor-pointer"
              >
                <span class="text-body-sm-strong text-ink"
                  >Target File Size</span
                >
                <span id="size-val" class="font-mono text-mute">1000 KB (1.0 MB)</span>
              </label>
              <input
                type="range"
                id="size-slider"
                min="100"
                max="10000"
                step="100"
                value="1000"
                class="w-full accent-primary h-1 bg-hairline rounded-lg appearance-none cursor-pointer focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-none"
                aria-label="Target File Size"
              />
              <div
                class="flex justify-between text-[10px] text-mute font-mono"
                aria-hidden="true"
              >
                <span>100 KB</span>
                <span>5,000 KB (5 MB)</span>
                <span>10,000 KB (10 MB)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Help Info Callout -->
          <div
            class="rounded p-4 bg-canvas-soft border border-hairline text-body-sm text-body space-y-2 shadow-level-1"
          >
            <div class="font-medium text-ink flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info text-link" aria-hidden="true"
              ></i>
              Visual Compression
            </div>
            <p>
              This tool compresses PDFs by downsampling and re-encoding embedded
              images. It works exceptionally well on <strong
                >scanned PDFs, presentations, and picture-heavy documents</strong
              >.
            </p>
            <p class="text-caption text-mute">
              Note: Text in compressed PDFs will be rasterized to ensure maximum
              compression. Original searchable text layer will not be preserved
              in this version.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Interactive Features Section -->
  <section
    id="features"
    class="py-16 md:py-20 px-4 md:px-6 border-t border-b border-hairline bg-canvas-soft-2/50 scroll-mt-[64px]"
  >
    <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto text-left">
      <div class="max-w-[600px] mb-12">
        <span
          class="text-caption-mono font-mono text-mute uppercase tracking-widest"
          >Architected for Privacy</span
        >
        <h2
          class="text-display-lg text-ink font-semibold tracking-[-0.8px] md:tracking-[-1.28px] mt-2 mb-4 leading-tight text-balance"
        >
          Engineered to be completely local.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-body-md text-body">
          Traditional PDF tools upload files to remote servers, putting
          sensitive documents at risk. Zcompressor runs all processes locally in
          your browser context.
        </p>
